<br>
Trial and error is a part of these guild events.  What works, what doesn't work, and WHEN IS IT TIME TO LEAVE?<br>
<br>
I enjoyed helping the 20's and 30's kill high level mobs and give them a chance to see what LGuk is like.  Note that this is an Adventure game and it was just that.  It was an adventure game until 6 or 7CST Saturday morning when we finally all got out and passed out.  Good or bad, we now know the power of 2 or 3 Wolf Packs in a dungoen.  We came in force and conqured (for 3 hourse that is).  I wouldn't ask the less seasoned Guild Members to attend an event that would lead to eventual death.  The mobs were reasonable and the adventure was all around us.<br>
<br>
I would especially like to thank the people that stayed on much longer than most for help with corpse retrieval and ressurections.  I did my best to get +49 resses and I think everyone that stuck around got one, maybe more than one :).<br>
<br>
Please don't be afraid to request a guild event.  I don't believe that all the planning that Teir is suggesting is required.  What is required is a strong presence and cooperation.  I we need to plan all the aspects of a raid, than maybe we need to assign someone to be a Project/Guild Event manager.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
<br>
Larou Gaea (ShadowKnight 47th Season) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003030><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/uteirwolfheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teir Wolfheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://eqforge.com/forums/icons/icon19.gif WIDTH=15 HEIGHT=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(10/25/00 12:54:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=297.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Of raids and things...</span><hr size=1> This post is something I had been writing up a few days before the Guk raid, Mol. It was not prompted by your raid. I can understand that the timing of the post can lead one to believe that it was specifically meant to be a general critque of Mol's raid, but that just isn't the case <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is also not meant to be a concrete policy for raid creation. Hence the line &quot;suggested guidelines.&quot; <br>
<br>
However, if Mol would like a comparison of the proposed guidelines with his raid, here's my take on it:<br>
<br>
1 ) The raid leader was unfamiliar with the hunting area.<br>
<br>
2 ) The raid goal was clearly defined. Everyone who entered Guk knew they were heading to the Noble.<br>
<br>
3 ) Lower Guk is a dangerous place for even a group of level 50s. Perhaps a level cut off of 35 would have been warranted.<br>
<br>
4 ) Group composition was pretty good. One of the challenges of a raid that spreads across multiple levels is creating groups of like level people that can adequately service the group and still get experience.<br>
<br>
5 ) Designating authorized pullers may very well have prevented the train that ended the raid.<br>
<br>
6 ) Someone didn't give the all important &quot;Evac, evac, evac!&quot; when it was seen that the train was more than the raiding party could handle. This would have at least gotten out the lower level folks.<br>
<br>
7 ) There was no planning for the worst case scenario of complete party wipe out resulting in a five hour corpse recovery. Why it was decided that resurections should have taken place in an openly hostile area rather than a controlable zone line *shrug*<br>
<br>
8 ) Post raid analysis... what we're doing now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Other than the hideous corpse recovery, I think the raid went rather well.<br>
<br>
I would like to thank Molotov for his raid. I would also like to thank Foodang, Larou and Ashrai for help with the final corpse recovery of Yonder, Kronenburg, Myrgrath, myself and themselves for the evening (or mid-morning as the case turned out to be)<br>
<br>
It saddens me that some folks have gone on the personal defensive after I made this post. My posting history and interactions with others would lead me to think folks would have seen this for what it really was... a general discussion about raid planning and implementation.<br>
