<br>
This is a very good example why we should all take care when making posts, you should always keep in mind the readers of your message and the context and timing of the message you are trying to communicate. But to be sure, specify what you are referring to so poor ol Molotov wont get his collar in a wad and not feel appreciated for the effort <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Everyone's fur (including mine) should now be neatly back in place and I can reflect on the Guk raid a little more.<br>
<br>
What really irritated me about the raid was not really the train and the death at the end, I cant count the number of times I have been in groups where we got wacked at the last moment of a raid and then had to do CR. But the CR on this particular raid was a real pain. I had planned on CR in the event of death but after we had been there for so long (much longer than planned) and many had left, the makeup of the group was seriously changed. It would have been a safe thing to just leave but I am sure everyone knows the tunnel vision (no pun intended) a group can get after its been camping a spot for many hours. There was only one cleric in the zone at 4 or 5 am and this cleric would have us pull all the corpses to a particular room then by the time we got there he had moved and wanted us to pull them to yet another and then again to yet another. This was really infuriating us because we would have to pull the corpses through mobs and we keep getting killed pulling corpses around. This went on for what seemed like hours, and finally the cleric just split on us and left us high and dry. I felt a collective sigh of relief from everyone when all the corpses where either resed or sitting at a safe zone at this point it seemed like 6 am. <br>
<br>
So this raid was good, but had a tough end that could have been avoided, but at 4 am its very easy to loose your focus and make mistakes. Either way I am going to sponsor another raid like I said and this one will be a very focused raid on one particular mob that is never camped easy to get to and very tough to kill. More to come……<br>
